  "texts": [
    "The accuracies achieved with 1500, 1200, and 1000 features for AlexNet, ResNet50, and DenseNet CNNs are significantly lower than those features obtained in Experiment II, where 4096, 2048, and 1920 features were used for AlexNet, ResNet50, and DenseNet CNNs.",
    "However, the accuracies achieved in Experiment II (Table 6) are higher except for ESD.",
    "The results indicate that the spectral information provided by DCT usually improves performance.",
    "In this experiment, all the extracted features from the three CNNs at the two selected training-testing ratios are fused using DCT.",
    "Different feature lengths are investigated to choose the optimum length that provides the best accuracy results."
